Haa... That child was also no good, huh... Why...
Why can't anyone understand my cooking...

Hmm... I'm in a bind... I'm running out of
options... Maybe I should try finding some random
girl on a matchmaking site... No, that's not it...

Um, excuse me. I heard a loud female voice from
here, was there something going on?

??? (Th-This person...! I can tell...! They're
from the other side...!)

??? (A once-in-a-lifetime opportunity...! I must
find a way to get their help...)

??? Ahem... Excuse me, I raised my voice because I
got into an argument with my assistant.

Oh, I see. So this is an assistant... \.\.Is this
some kind of cooking class?

Soujirou: Yes, I am Soujirou, a cooking researcher
who is here to provide cooking guidance.

Eh...?! Soujirou-san, is that you...!? I actually
have a few of your recipe books!

I often rely on you because I can easily make
delicious dishes!

Soujirou: Ah... that popular trashy book...
*muttering*

Soujirou: No, please don't mind it. It was just a
muttering. Anyway, would you listen to my worries?

Soujirou-san's worries...? Oh! If it's okay with
me, I'll listen.

Soujirou: Actually... I've had a dish that I've
wanted to make for a long time, but it just won't
come together.
Even though you're so good at cooking?

Soujirou: I think my cooking skills are quite
something. However... the dish I have in mind is
something that can only be understood by having a
woman taste it.

Soujirou: Yes, the cooking I aspire to can be
succinctly described as a 'seductive dish' that
captivates the woman who tastes it.

Seductive cooking...? But someone as skilled as
Soujirou-san can surely create elegant dishes...

Soujirou: That's not enough! I want to create
dishes that make you conscious of the person who
cooked it and make your heart race from the moment
you take a bite... I want to create dishes at that
level!

Soujirou: Please...! It's been my dream for a long
time...! Please... help me!

Hehe... You're more passionate about cooking than
what I see on TV, huh?

If I can be of any help, I'll gladly cooperate as
much as possible.

Soujirou: I'm glad... I sincerely appreciate
it...!

Soujirou: Well then... I didn't ask for your name,
did I?

I'm Ayako Nagatsuki. Please call me by my first
name. I'm more used to that.

Soujirou: Understood. Then, Ayako-san. You can
come for a taste test whenever you like.

Soujirou: If you come, I'll prepare it right away.
Oh, of course, I won't charge you anything.

Eh~ Is it really okay for me to eat delicious food
for free?

Soujirou: Yes, in return, I may ask you about the
texture, taste, and aroma of the food from time to
time, so please bear with me on that.

(Hehe... Being able to eat delicious food for free
and even gather faith... seems like a good
deal...)

(I can't believe I got this lucky. Alright, with
this, I can keep pushing forward.)
(Let's meet again when we have time.)

Soujirou: Hello. Would you like to taste my
cooking?
